# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Environment variables template.
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   1. Copy this file to `.env.local` in the same `web/` folder:  cp .env.example .env.local
#   2. Fill in the real values on the right of each `=` (no quotes, no spaces around `=`).
#   3. Restart the dev server (`npm run dev`) so Next.js picks the values up.
#
# `.env.local` is gitignored and must NEVER be committed — it holds real secrets.
# This `.env.example` carries NO real values and IS committed, so the next person
# knows which variables to set.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Moralis API key — powers wallet-tracker token detail on BNB Chain & Avalanche
# (chains with no keyless token source). Free tier is enough.
# Get one at: https://admin.moralis.io  → create a project → copy the API key.
# Server-side only; never exposed to the browser. If unset, those two chains show
# balance only (no token breakdown) — nothing else breaks.
MORALIS_API_KEY=

# ── Supabase — the Openview project (koedodxkryyxizcryggy) ──
#
# Powers the Reports feature (§17) AND the keep-alive cron. Schema: web/supabase/schema.sql —
# apply it in the SQL editor before these do anything.
#
# NOTE: this is NOT the project the global SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF env var points at — that one is
# UDG's music-events app. If you see venues/artists/events tables, you're on the wrong project.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
# The anon / "publishable" key. Safe in the browser: RLS grants it SELECT and nothing else.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
# The service_role / "secret" key. Server-side ONLY — it bypasses RLS entirely, so anyone holding
# it has full read/write. NEVER prefix this NEXT_PUBLIC_ (that ships it to every browser).
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# Bearer token Vercel sends when triggering a cron; both cron routes require it when set.
# MUST be plain ASCII — generate with `openssl rand -hex 32`. A pasted em-dash or curly quote
# cannot be sent in an HTTP header at all, so no caller could ever authenticate (the routes detect
# this and return "cron secret misconfigured" rather than a misleading 401). See ARCHITECTURE §17.4.
CRON_SECRET=

# ── Reports (/home/reports) — the AI market reports. See ARCHITECTURE.md §17 ──
#
# Without these the reports still build and render: the gainer tables, Binance pairs and sentiment
# all work, and the analysis section simply says "Analysis unavailable" rather than inventing one.
# So these are optional — they only add the written commentary.
#
# GEMINI_API_KEY — primary. Free tier is ~1,500 requests/day and the reports need 3/day, so the
#   free tier is ample. Get one at https://aistudio.google.com/apikey (no card required).
GEMINI_API_KEY=
#
# GROQ_API_KEY — fallback, used ONLY when Gemini returns 429 (free-tier quota exhausted).
#   Free, no card: https://console.groq.com/keys
GROQ_API_KEY=
#
# Both are server-side only and must never be prefixed NEXT_PUBLIC_ — that would ship the key to
# the browser, where anyone can read it out of the JS bundle (F12) and spend your quota.

# ── Reports: local testing escape hatches (leave unset in production) ──
# Point the LLM calls at a local mock so the analysis path can be exercised without a real key or
# burning quota. Unset => the real endpoints.
# GEMINI_BASE_URL=
# GROQ_BASE_URL=
